{
  "text": "Approximately two weeks after the baseline survey, participants received a tailored feedback report that introduced the program and provided personalized health messages incorporating their responses to the survey. Shortly thereafter, telephone counseling calls were initiated by health educators, which were also tailored to the participants, and relied on motivational interviewing techniques [CITATION_1] . The outcome of the health educator calls is the binary repeated measure Y, which is subject to missingness (e.g., no answer, answering machine) where,",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "12848168"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "12848168": {
      "title": "Tools for health: The efficacy of a tailored intervention targeted for construction laborers",
      "abstract": "Objectives ::: Novel approaches to worksite health promotion are needed for high-risk workers who change job sites frequently, and thus may have limited access to worksite health promotion efforts. The objective of this study was to test a behavioral intervention among construction laborers."
    }
  }
}